8. style.css  (the look and feel)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Plain CSS — no frameworks, no build step needed.

  body uses flexbox to center the card both horizontally and
  vertically on the page, regardless of screen size.

  .card is the white rounded box containing everything. Its
  box-shadow gives it a subtle floating appearance.

  .field input:focus uses an indigo outline glow to clearly
  show which field the keyboard is in (important for
  accessibility).

  .alert-error / .alert-success are the red and green
  banner styles shown for login failures and logouts.

  .btn-primary is the indigo "Sign in" button.
  .btn-secondary is the lighter "Sign out" button on the
  dashboard.


